The paper focuses on vision-based robotic grasping, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) that heavily relies on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also discusses deep learning-based methods (cs.LG) for grasp detection and motion planning, and reinforcement learning-based methods (cs.SY) for motion planning. Therefore, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.SY are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
